gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Knicks 109, Cavaliers 91
gameRecap.excerpt: The Knicks defeated the Cavaliers, 109-91. Jalen Brunson recorded 19 points, five rebounds, and two assists for the Knicks, while Julius Randle added 19 points and 10 rebounds in the victory. Donovan Mitchell tallied 26 points, three assists, and three rebounds for the Cavaliers in the losing effort. The Knicks improve to 2-2 on the season, while the Cavaliers fall to 1-3.
